Seriki Adinoyi in Jos Two persons have been reported dead after they were drown in the dam in Rayfield Resort, Jos, Plateau State. THISDAY gathered that the victims: Mr. Michael Nyam and Mr. Elijah Solomon were both residents of Rayfield community, who got drown on Saturday while trying to get back the shoes of one of their friends that fell into the dam. An eye witness, Mr. Gyang Pwol, explained that “they jumped into the deep area of the dam to rescue a shoe of their friend but unfortunately, the volume of water was too much.” Pwol, who also confirmed that their remains had been buried, did not give further details. The Police Public Relation Officer of Plateau Police Command, Mr. Gabriel Ogaba, however, said that the incident has not been reported to the command.